Flames shot out of Thassalin's throat as the enormous Thraki circled a particular forest clearing, setting it under surveillance to spot any movements. Strangely, the eerie screeching behind him subsided as he slowed down. Thassalin had forgotten about the passengers on his back.
“What’s this, Tenuk, you’ve already transformed into a Thraki once!”
“Flying on my own is very different from being suddenly lifted up by a huge pink dragon!”
“It wasn’t that bad, was it, Kayel?”
Kayel clearly did not share Nyssis' opinion. He looked less black than usual, and his claws had dug so deeply into Thassalin's back that the Thraki was bleeding. However, Thassalin seemed to be unaffected by this. Still, he realized that he had frightened his new friends and landed on a clearing.
“I AM SORRY, BUT I SMELTED SOMETHING. I HAD TO CHECK IT OUT!”
“But did you have to drag us along?”
“He'll come up with something…”, grunted Nyssis.
“True, but can Retvik drive?”
Nyssis winked and turned back to Tenuk.
“Hast du Retvik schon einmal ein Fahrzeug fahren sehen? Er hat keinen Truck wie du, und ich habe ihn auch noch kein schickes kleines Auto wie das von Kayel fahren sehen. Außerdem fing er auch nur an, das Auto für die Arbeit zu nehmen, weil du uns immer fährst. Er hat nur sein Fahrrad.”
Schallendes Gelächter unterbrach sie. Thassalin schien plötzlich etwas wahnsinnig komisch zu finden, aber keiner wusste, worüber er lachte. Es dauerte ein bisschen zu lang, bis sich Thassalin beruhigt hatte.
“ES TUT MIR LEID, ABER ICH HABE MIR EUREN RIESIGEN FREUND IN RÜSTUNG AUF SO EINEM WINZIG KLEINEN FAHRRAD FÜR TEMTHAN-KINDER VORGESTELLT. DAS WAR ZUM TOTLACHEN! ICH WÜNSCHTE, ICH HÄTTE IRGEND EINE ART TELEPATHIE. EINE HERRLICHER VORSTELLUNG! EINE, DIE ICH NICHT TEILEN KANN!”
Kayel kicherte, da er sich denken konnte, was in Thassalins Kopf vorging. „Ja, stimmt schon. Aber was hast du gerochen, und warum bist du so plötzlich losgeflogen?”
Thassalin grunzte, hob ab und verschwand. Als er nach kurzer Zeit zurückkehrte, warf er Nyssi etwas Lebloses vor die Füße. Es war ein Orothrack, ein sehr seltenes, goldweißes Drachengeschöpf. Aber ihm fehlte der Kopf. „NOCH EIN TOTER. ICH HÖRE IHRE SCHREIE. RIECHE IHR BLUT. ETWAS DRÄNGT MICH, ZU SCHÜTZEN UND ZU JAGEN. WIE YISINI ES BEFIELT. SIE SIND GANZ NAH.”
The mighty Thraki suddenly froze. Nyssi and Kayel also froze and looked attentively at a gap in the clearing. Something large and black stared at them and snarled. Whatever it was, it spread two enormous wings and charged at Thassalin, ignoring the three smaller beings in between. Kayel and Tenuk just managed to take cover, but Nyssi was dragged along and almost hurled onto Thassalin.
Thassalin reacted to this attack by grabbing Nyssi and tossing him onto his back with his unbelievably long, nimble tail before he himself took off into the air. The black, double-winged creature followed them at high speed.
Kayel snapped irritably, while he took his rifle off his back and opened a bag that contained a ammunition belt. He slung the belt over his chest, but quickly realized that Nyssi, the Thraki, and the monster were out of sight.
“Hey, Tenuk, could you transform into something that can fly?” asked Kayel.
“You want to pursue them?”
“Yes, of course!”
“But… One of them is a giant monster!”
“Yes and? I'm standing here with a high-caliber rifle in hand and could shoot immediately. But, well, how should I put it – I would need to be able to see it to hit it.”
Tenuk hesitated, then stepped back to gain more space. With a soft, painful grunt, Tenuk's body stretched, his fur turned into scales, and his arms transformed into wings. He rapidly changed into a normal light blue Thraki, but his eyes remained red.
“Get on.”
Like a normally appearing Thraki, Tenuk now had a proper scaled shield running along his back. Conveniently, he also had a pair of spikes on his back where Kayel could hang on. It took Tenuk a little too long to get airborne, but once in the air, he quickly oriented himself and tried to take up the pursuit.
Tenuk and Kayel soon realized they weren't alone. A second dark creature shot up beneath them, and Tenuk barely avoided a collision.
“Is that the other intimidating giant monster Lanex was afraid of?” Kayel furrowed his brow. He tried to aim at the second beast, missed, and quickly reloaded.
Tenuk didn't respond. He was too busy focusing on the flight towards Nyssi and Thassalin, even though the other beast was following them. Kayel awkwardly turned around to keep the monster in sight. The fact that it was following them was an advantage for Kayel because it made it easier for him to aim and fire. Two shots went through the upper wings of the beast. It screamed in pain and sank back under the trees. Kayel wasn't sure if it was still following them, but it wouldn't be able to keep up with them.
A good distance ahead, Nyssi clung desperately while Thassalin thrashed and spat flames at the blackened monster. The creature was definitely injured. It appeared furious but not ready to give up. The fireballs didn't seem to have the desired effect. As Thassalin stretched out, Nyssi seized the opportunity to draw her own weapon, an old shotgun. Although not necessarily the first choice, maybe the buckshot would scare off the black beast.
